    "title": "Immediate Requirement Store Manager at Easyday International Enterprises",
    "description": "Join the Easyday International Enterprises family as a Store Manager in Amritsar. We believe in empowering our employees with the tools, training, and environment they need to succeed.\n\nAbout Easyday International Enterprises:\nEasyday International Enterprises is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Build relationships with regular customers to drive loyalty\n• Conduct regular stock audits and prevent pilferage\n• Handle customer queries, complaints, and escalations effectively\n• Manage store operations to ensure smooth daily functioning\n• Achieve sales targets and improve store performance metrics\n• Assist in recruiting, onboarding, and performance management of staff\n• Monitor inventory levels and coordinate replenishment activities\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Chartered Accountant (ICAI)\n• 1-3 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in KPI Management\n• Proficiency in SAP Retail\n• Proficiency in Team Leadership\n• Proficiency in Retail Operations\n• Proficiency in Category Management\n• Proficiency in E-commerce Integration\n• Proficiency in MS Excel\n• Proficiency in CRM\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Meal coupons and food allowance\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Company-sponsored certifications\n• Life and accident insurance\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Salary Range: 4 LPA - 9 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Amritsar, Punjab, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Easyday International Enterprises!",
